snippet.title: Sky News Breakfast: Racing to stop the variant spread
snippet.description:
On Sky News Breakfast this morning,

- Concern grows about the new COVID variant, as British nationals in Southern Africa rush home,

- A man's killed in Northern Ireland, and tens of thousands of homes are left without power in Scotland, as Storm Arwen sweeps across the UK,

- The family of a 24 year old Iraqi Kurd who died while trying to join her fiancé in Britain warn others against the journey,

- And tributes to Stephen Sondheim, the man who re-invented the musical, who's died at the age of 91.
